Class usage.DiskData extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: 5394909818404147396L

Serialized Fields

major

java.lang.String major
The major number of the devide with this partition.

minor

java.lang.String minor
The minor number of the device with this partition. This serves to separate the partitions into different physical devices and relates to the number at the end of the name of the partition.

name

java.lang.String name
The name of the partition.

readsCompleted

long readsCompleted
This is the total number of reads completed successfully.

readsMerged

long readsMerged
Reads and writes which are adjacent to each other may be merged for efficiency. thus two 4K reads may become one 8K read before it is ultimately handed to the disk, and so it will be counted (and queued).

writesMerged

long writesMerged
See numberReadsMerged documentation.

sectorsRead

long sectorsRead
This is the total number of sector read successfully.

millisecondsReading

long millisecondsReading
This is the total number of millisecoPartitionnds spent by all reads (as measured from __make_request() to end_that_request_last() ).

writesCompleted

long writesCompleted
This is the total number of writes completed successfully.

sectorsWritten

long sectorsWritten
This is the total number of sectors written successfully.

millisecondsWriting

long millisecondsWriting
This is the total number of milliseconds spent by all writes (as measured from __make_request() to end_that_request_last() ).

iosInProgress

long iosInProgress
The only field that should go to zero. Incremented as requests are given to appropriate struct request_queue and decremented as they finish.

millisecondsSpentInIO

long millisecondsSpentInIO
This field increases so long as field IOs currently in progress is nonzero.

weightedMillisecondsDoingIO

long weightedMillisecondsDoingIO
This field is incremented at each I/O start, I/O completion, I/O merge, or read of these stats by the number of I/Os Partitionin progress times the number of milliseconds spent doing I/O since the last update of this field. This can provide an easy measure of both I/O completion time and the backlog that may be accumulating.

Class usage.MemData extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: 8926305540190678396L

Serialized Fields

size

int size
Total number of pages of memory (total program size in kilobytes).

resident

int resident
Resident set size.

share

int share
Number of pages of shared (mmap'd) memory

text

int text
Number of pages that are code (text).

data

int data
Number of pages of data + stack.

vsize

java.lang.String vsize
Virtual memory size in bytes (/proc/[pid]/stat).

rss

int rss
Resident set number of pages the process has in real memory. This is just the pages which count toward text, data, or stack space. This does not include pages which have not been demand-loaded in, or which are swapped out (/proc/[pid]/stat).

rsslim

java.lang.String rsslim
Current limit (in bytes) of the rss of the process; usually 2,147,483,647 (/proc/[pid]/stat).

memTotal

int memTotal
Total memory phisicaly instaled in the system. This is not a usage information, however, can be useful to calculate metrics over the process, in KB.

memUsed

int memUsed
Total memory being used by the hole system, not only the WattDB process, in kilobytes.

memFree

int memFree
The amount of physical RAM, in kilobytes, left unused by the system.

memBuffers

int memBuffers
The amount of physical RAM, in kilobytes, used for file buffers.

memCached

int memCached
The amount of physical RAM, in kilobytes, used as cache memory.
